      • searchPlantsInArr

        public java.util.HashMap<java.lang.String,Plant> searchPlantsInArr(java.lang.String query,
                                                                   java.util.ArrayList<Plant> plantList)
        Search a given array of plants and return an array of all Plants that match the query. If the query matches the latin or any of the common names, that plant is returned.

        Comparators can be used on the results.
        Parameters:
        query - Simple, non-regex query where the query can appear anywhere in the plant latin or common name. plantList which are the plants to search thru.
        Returns:
        null if no matching results, a Plant array of all matching results.

      • startNewSession

        public boolean startNewSession()
                        throws java.lang.Exception
        Start a brand new Session, and save the old one at it's last saved location, if it has one.
        Returns:
        False if there is no last saved file path, and the UI needs to ask the user where to save it. True if successful in loading new session.
        Throws:
        java.lang.Exception - if it failed to save the current session, ask the user again.

      • startNewSessionFromSavedSession

                                        throws java.lang.Exception
        Start a new Session from one that was previously saved to disk.
        Parameters:
        filepath - Relative filepath of the save.
        Returns:
        False if there is no last saved file path, and the UI needs to ask the user where to save it. True if successful in loading new session.
        Throws:
        java.lang.Exception - if it failed to save the current session, ask the user again.

      • saveSession

        public boolean saveSession()
                    throws java.lang.Exception
        Save the current session. Throws an exception if Model doesn't know where to save to.
        Returns:
        True if successful (with disk) in saving. False if not.
        Throws:
        java.lang.Exception - When there is no lastSavedFilepath specified in the Session, and the UI needs to prompt the user to ask where to save to.
        See Also:
        #saveSession(String) saveSession}

      • saveSession

        public boolean saveSession(java.lang.String filepath)

        NOTE: This does not add the extension .gardenproject to the save file, you must specify that manually in the JavaFX FileChooser as the default extension.
